Greenspan Says ‘Euro Is Breaking Down,’ Questions Bank-Collateral Quality

-- B y   J o s h u a   Z u m b r u n
-- 
2011-08-23T13:27:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-23/greenspan-says-euro-is-breaking-down-questions-bank-collateral-quality.html
Former Federal Reserve Chairman  Alan
Greenspan  said today that “the euro is breaking down” and that
some collateral held by euro-area banks is questionable.
Greenspan was speaking at a forum in  Washington .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Joshua Zumbrun in Washington at 
